    <item>
      <title>Rigidbody Constraint-based Physics Simulation</title>
      <link>https://jingyulee.com/project/rigidbody-constraint-based-physics-simulation/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 14 Jan 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://jingyulee.com/project/rigidbody-constraint-based-physics-simulation/</guid>
      <description>
&lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;iframe src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/S31Hpw_fuUE&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; allowfullscreen title=&#34;YouTube Video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was my personal project that I implemented from scratch for CS550(Physics Simulation) class at DigiPen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Accomplishments:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gilbert%E2%80%93Johnson%E2%80%93Keerthi_distance_algorithm&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;GJK&lt;/a&gt; for convex collision checking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;EPA for collision record generation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GJK Simplex visualization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;EPA Polytope visualization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Constraints-based using Sequential Impulse solver, developed by Erin Catto&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contact caching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Warm starting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Baumgarte stabilization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Friction and restitution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
